ey for trustees. He wants more money\nfor junkets. He wants more money for super�intendents. ","index":"00353","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We\nwant $40 million more in the classroom, where it can help the children instead:\nbetter outcomes, better results and better futures for all Manitoba\nschoolchildren. ","index":"00354","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDougald </b><b><a name=\"_Toc70394489\">Lamont</a></b><b>�(St.\nBoniface):</b> The National Advisory Committee on Immunization, or NACI, has\nclear priorities for key populations in stage 2 and stage&nbsp;3 of its\nrecommendations. ","index":"00355","speaker":"Dougald Lamont"},{"html":"����� Right\nafter first responders�who include para�medics, firefighters and police�the\nnext in line are supposed to be front-line essential workers who can't work\nvirtually: people working in education, early child�hood educators and transit\nworkers, essential caregivers for vulnerable people and individuals aged&nbsp;16\nto 59 with a underlying medical condition. ","index":"00356","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Is\nthis government going to follow NACI's advice and make those people a vaccine\npriority, and if not, why not? ","index":"00357","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nBrian </b><b><a name=\"_Toc70394490\">Pallister</a></b><b>�(Premier):</b>\nI appreciate the question. I think that we're doing our best to have a system\nthat benefits Manitobans in vulnerable areas, in particular, and to get the age\ndown and the access down and to promote vaccine use. ","index":"00358","speaker":"Brian Pallister"},{"html":"����� I thank\nthe members opposite. The member from Union Station, I know, is putting up\nposters in her area to encourage people to go and get vaccinated. The member\nfor St. Johns (Ms. Fontaine) has made the effort�sincere effort�to try to get\nmore people vac�cinated. These are positive, positive efforts that MLAs can\nundertake together to make sure that we get more folks vaccinated in our\nprovince. That's the big challenge. ","index":"00359","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This\nis a race between variants and vaccines. Up until now the vaccines haven't been\nwinning but we want to get more people vaccinated because that's how we get\nManitoba their lives back. ","index":"00360","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> The honourable member for St. Boniface, on a supplementary\nquestion. ","index":"00361","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDougald </b><b><a name=\"_Toc70394492\">Lamont</a></b><b>�(St.\nBoniface):</b> There are over 2,000 active COVID‑19 cases in Manitoba and\nhundreds of cases�new cases�a day. There are warnings from ERs, ICUs and\nhospitals that staff are already run ragged. We are on the same path we were on\nin October, and this government is forcing the same choice on people: either\nstay home and go broke, or work and get COVID. And given that choice, of course\nManitobans' mental health is suffering. ","index":"00362","speaker":"Dougald Lamont"},{"html":"����� No one\nis saying there should be no economy. We're saying that if the government\norders someone to stop working, you better make sure that you can pay�they can\npay their bills, so there's an economy to come back to when this crisis is\nover. ","index":"00363","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We're\ngetting greater restrictions. ","index":"00364","speaker":""},{"html":"����� When\nis this government going to give Manitobans the greater financial supports they\nwant, need and deserve?","index":"00365","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nBrian </b><b><a name=\"_Toc70394493\">Pallister</a></b><b>�(Premier):</b>\nLargest supports for small business in Canada, according to my friend, Molly\nMcCracken, who says we're second only to BC on individual supports. So I answer\nthat question. ","index":"00366","speaker":"Brian Pallister"},{"html":"����� What I\nwill say to the member is that the federal Liberals have demonstrated a patent\ndisrespect for women. When they put Jonathan Vance in charge of the mission t